    {
      "title": "Translate the equation down",
      "content": "Translating the graph down $5$ units means replace $y$ with $y+5$ in the original equation.<br/>$$7x-8(y+5)=19$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Simplify the translated line",
      "content": "Expand and simplify.<br/>$$7x-8y-40=19$$<br/>$$7x-8y=59$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Find the horizontal intercept",
      "content": "At the $x$-intercept, $y=0$.<br/>$$7x-8(0)=59$$<br/>$$x=\\frac{59}{7}$$<br/>The answer is <strong>59/7</strong>."
